In this article, President Donald Trump proclaims November 2018 as National Family Caregivers Month. He pays tribute to the millions of Americans who selflessly care for family members who are chronically ill, elderly, or have a disability. The article emphasizes the challenges of caregiving and celebrates the joy of providing support and comfort to loved ones. Trump expresses gratitude to family caregivers for their daily work in ensuring their loved ones can live in their homes and communities. The article mentions the RAISE Family Caregivers Act, signed into law earlier in the year, which aims to support family caregivers by developing strategies and establishing an advisory council. The Supporting Grandparents Raising Grandchildren Act, also signed by Trump, addresses the growing number of people caring for grandchildren due to the opioid crisis. The article concludes by acknowledging the dedication and compassion of family caregivers and encouraging all Americans to express gratitude to them.